# Decision Log Rule

Use this rule when the user asks to log a decision, record an architecture choice, or preserve reasoning behind a tradeoff.

## Task

Create an ADR-style Markdown note.

## Instructions

- Be explicit about the decision.
- Preserve why this option won.
- Include rejected alternatives.
- Include consequences and revisit triggers.
- Be terse but complete.

## Output schema

```md
---
id: ADR-YYYY-MM-DD-slug
title: "..."
date: YYYY-MM-DD
source_tool: cursor
source_project: repo-name
tags: [adr, architecture]
status: active
---

# Title

## Context
- 

## Decision
- 

## Alternatives considered
- Option A:
- Option B:

## Consequences
- Positive:
- Negative:

## Revisit when
- 

## Related notes
- [[...]]
```

## Success criteria

A future reader should understand not just what was chosen, but why.
